title: Grateful Dead Live at Pauley Pavilion, UCLA on 1980-06-29
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway, Promised Land, Loser, Minglewood Blues, Althea, Looks Like Rain, Easy To Love You, Big Railroad Blues-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Deal

Set 2

Feel Like A Stranger, Don't Ease Me In, Estimated Prophet-> Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Drums*-> The Other One*-> Black Peter*-> Sugar Magnolia*, E: U.S. Blues

*W Lee Oskar

reviews.review_text: Not Bad Not a bad recording at all, reason I would even say not bad is over the years have heard many copy's. This one is ok. Not outstanding but ok. For those of us who prefer an Aud tape this is one I would grab at this point. Around the 7 minute mark the boys pull off the tribal beat during stranger. Often heard in 80's Feel like a strange.I realize this is THE Scarlet > Fire many claim to be one of hottest of 1980. It is good and hot.3 stars because highend is missing not much hiss either
- In all, an OK show made really good by the presence of Mr Oskar. The nice end of a really lame month. Not a single show in June this year rated a 5, in my opinion.
thought it was a good show it had special meaning for me...just moved to SoCal that day from Phoenix, and caught the show that night. i liked it.
1980 Jerry Garcia This is a good show from an excellent period, 5/1 and 9/6/80. June is a non-issue in an isolated fashion. The first set is full on.

My First time in California that day ! I taped w Mason , ( RIP ) and (Gus) ,it may have been us three.                As for day one in California, is a day I'll never forget! A picture perfect,LA day . Grass greener than f, weed flowing , a different.....vibe big time, then Jersey!!!!! Thank God for People's Express, sold that surf board and went the next day! The rest was history, San Diego was a police show the next night w band members being hassled ,and the crowd. Estimated into Scarlet into fire , yes it was a magical show w moments of extreme excellence and some just good ole , GD .
       The next day in LA, I somehow ?????, was able someehere to be in the printing shop that produced the Alaska Posters ? I left w the last eight of em , practically free🤔😄. That was crazy. A trip etched in my ,DNA .
